The Company refers to this system concept as the Multiple-Input, Multiple-Output Intermodulation Spread Spectrum (MIMO-ISS) System.  The MIMO-ISS System is a non-linear digital communications product technology. The product technology targets next-generation, 5G global cellular markets. As a 5G product portfolio concept, the MIMO-ISS System targets applications including: 5G services, automotive radar, internet-of-things applications, agile and robust networking, and “smart city” networks. MIMO-ISS is proprietary and patent pending. The integrated product portfolio is composed of three core technology systems. These core technology systems are the following: (1) the MIMO-ISS Waveform System, (2) the MIMO-DPR Radar System, and (3) the MIMO-CRN Networking System.

Description: Detroit SOUP is a microgranting dinner that celebrates and supports creative projects in Detroit.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Detroit Area, Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: Detroit SOUP is a microgranting dinner that celebrates and supports creative projects in Detroit. At the event, attendees eat, talk, share resources, and vote on their favorite projects. For a donation of $5 attendees receive soup, salad, bread, and a vote as well as an opportunity to hear from four presentations ranging from art, urban agriculture, social justice, social entrepreneurs, education, technology, and more. Each presenter has four minutes to share their idea and answer four questions from the audience. At the end of the night, the ballots are counted and a winner is chosen. Winners collect their money, launch their projects, and attend a future SOUP dinner to report their project’s progress. Detroit SOUP was founded by [Amy Kaherl](https://www.crunchbase.com/person/amy-kaherl) in 2010 and is based in Detroit, Michigan.
